<paragraph blockId="9.[151,684,1520,1669]" lastBlockId="9.[714,1247,170,289]" pageId="9" pageNumber="76">
<taxonomicName box="[177,349,1520,1545]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Celastraceae" genus="Brexia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Celastrales" pageId="9" pageNumber="76" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coursiana">
<emphasis box="[177,349,1520,1545]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="76">Brexia coursiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a sparsely branched shrub to treelet in mid-elevation subhumid forest from the region of Zahamena PN/RNI (Fig. 5). It can be recognized by its leaves with an acute apex, inflorescences usually borne on the main stem (cauli- flory), slender peduncles less than 
<quantity box="[1106,1173,170,197]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="76" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
broad with secondary axes branching well below the apex, a distinctly 5-lobed calyx, and petaloid disc segments with an irregularly laciniate margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[714,1247,324,473]" pageId="9" pageNumber="76">
CONSERVATION STATUS. — With an AO of 
<quantity box="[714,802,355,381]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="76" unit="km" value="200.0">200 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[803,813,350,369]" fontSize="8" pageId="9" pageNumber="76">2</superScript>
, and only 2 subpopulations, both of which are encompassed within the Zahamena protected area, 
<taxonomicName box="[881,1054,416,441]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Celastraceae" genus="Brexia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Celastrales" pageId="9" pageNumber="76" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coursiana">
<emphasis box="[881,1054,416,441]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="76">Brexia coursiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is assigned a preliminary status of Endangered (EN B1ab2ab).
</paragraph>
